title: Naran
subTitle: Velayudhan, an orphan, is loved by the villagers as he keeps the village free from unsavoury people and practices. However, an evil moneylender and politician get jealous and try to get rid of him.

title: Finger Print
subTitle: A patriarch of a royal family goes on a mission to find the murderers responsible for killing his descendant. He takes the help of his nephews who are police officers.

title: The Great Indian Kitchen
subTitle: A newly married woman tries to become an ideal wife and daughter-in-law to her traditional and patriarchy family. Eventually, their growing demands and disrespect cause rifts between them.

title: Hareendran Oru Nishkalankan
subTitle: Hareendran, a software tycoon, runs a successful company with his childhood friend. However, things take an unexpected turn when his friend damages his reputation.

title: Chirikkum Thalika
subTitle: A comprehensive compilation of some of the best rib-tickling comedy scenes from various Malayalam movies featuring renowned actors and actresses.

title: Johny Johny Yes Appa
subTitle: Johny pretends to be a gentleman but is a thief who thrives on lies and betrayals. His life turns upside down after his encounter with Adam, an orphan.

title: Minnal Murali
subTitle: Jaison, a young tailor, gains superpowers after being struck by lightning. However, he must thwart the evil intentions of an unexpected adversary to become the superhero that his rural village needs.

title: Bro Daddy
subTitle: Two close friends, John and Kurian, wish to take their friendship one step further and get their children married. However, they are unaware of the lives their children lead in the city.

title: Grrr...
subTitle: Heartbroken and intoxicated, Rejimon stumbles into a lion's den at the zoo. Haridas, a guard, has to forcefully dive in to rescue him, earning media attention for the blunder.

title: Oru Marubhoomikkadha
subTitle: Madhavan is an honest and hardworking man. However, when a rich man's daughter, Eliana, asks him to abduct her and demand a ransom from her father, his life turns upside down.

title: Maniyarayile Ashokan
subTitle: Ashokan desperately wishes to get married as he is past the marriageable age. However, bad luck and a series of unfortunate circumstances threaten to make this a distant dream.

title: Maniyarayile Ashokan

title: Paradesi
subTitle: Raasa, a carefree young man from a village, is lured into working at a British tea plantation. However, once he gets there, the realisation of an unconditional slavery ruins his life.

title: Pachuvum Kovalanum
subTitle: For TV director Thomaskutty Pachu, nothing is more stressful than dealing with his pesky cousin Joseph Kovalan. That is, until a murder occurs on the set.

title: Aagathan
subTitle: En route to Bangalore, a man falls in love with a beautiful girl. But he soon realises that her father was responsible for the death of his sister during a terrorist attack a long time ago.

title: Alibhai
subTitle: Ali Bhai, a goon, is the saviour of the poor in his dominion, Palayam market. However, when his enemies try to take over the market, he goes to great lengths to protect his stronghold and his people.

title: Thrissur Pooram
subTitle: Pullu Giri is trying to live a peaceful life and forget his ruffian past. Following an incident, he gets dragged into the affairs of some local gangs.

title: Evidam Swargamanu
subTitle: Mathews owns a farm that is the envy of everyone in the village. It attracts the attention of a dirty land dealer, who entangles him in a vicious bureaucratic web to take it away from him.

title: Local Boys
subTitle: The students of two schools consider each other as rivals and constantly keep fighting. However, Professor John tries to guide the students towards the right path.

title: Hridayam
subTitle: Arun, a young man, enrols in an engineering college but falls prey to bad habits. As he grows up, he decides to turn over a new leaf and become a responsible adult.

title: Sudani From Nigeria
subTitle: Majeed, a football coach in Malappuram, recuits Nigerian players for his local team. When star player Samuel is injured, he stays with Majeed, leading to a deep bond despite cultural differences.

title: Punyam Aham
subTitle: Narayan's mother separated from her Brahmin husband years ago. But Narayan sets out to find him, in order to uncover his own identity in the society.

title: Aayudham
subTitle: When a powerful explosion occurs at the Vilayam beach seconds after Chief Minister Madhavan leaves the venue, Police Officer Rishikesh is tasked with the investigation to find the truth behind the blast.

title: Abraham Lincoln
subTitle: Abraham and Lincoln are drawn into a turbulent world of crime and loyalty, where personal choices and past ties shape their unpredictable path.

title: Paachuvum Albhuthavilakkum
subTitle: A young man's cross-country trip with his landlord's grandmother propels him into a journey of unexpected experiences and self-discovery.

title: Dhrona
subTitle: A man sets out to investigate the death of his brother at a haunted house, leading him to come across several supernatural experiences.

title: Vettam
subTitle: Gopalakrishnan meets Veena while trying to smuggle a stolen necklace. Later, he accompanies Veena on her mission to unite with her lover.

title: Kilometers and Kilometers
subTitle: A poor tour guide from Kerala takes an American client on a journey through India. During their travels, the changing landscapes and experiences help them reshape their understanding of each other.

title: Swapnakoodu
subTitle: Three men compete against each other to win the affections of a beautiful woman. However, complications arise when her mother suffers from a heart attack.

title: The Priest
